eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede may perform her mayoral duties according to the Durban Magistrate's Court's ruling on Thursday. Courtesy of #DSTV403 DURBAN - eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede may perform her mayoral duties, according to the Durban magistrate's court's ruling on Thursday. Gumede faces charges of fraud, racketeering and money laundering. Her case has been postponed to January next year for further investigation. READ: Zandile Gumede disappointed at case postponement The decision over Gumede being placed on special leave was not up to the court. The provincial spokesperson, Ricardo Mthembu, said the ANC is dealing with a number of people who have been accused of misconduct. "We are going to deal with these issues looking at the report and make a decision on Sunday."